So, the `compactBuffer()` is only called when we have read a quarter of the `TCP_BUFFER` and this makes the problem much smaller than described above. We would still benefit from using a ring buffer but that is likely only going to reduce jitter and not the performance so much. I am closing this now.

```
        } else if (inBBB.readPosition() > TCP_BUFFER / 4) {
            compactBuffer();
            busy = true;
        }
```
